The paper deals with mathematical formulations and properties of the qualitative uncertainty principle (QUP) in the context of harmonic analysis, which is a subfield of signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of integral operators and their properties, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the use of operator families and sparse representation, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the paper involves the study of the Fourier transform, Wigner-Ville distribution, Gabor transform, and wavelet, which are all topics in signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT).
